@Database Changes_To_V1.11.guide

@Node Main "Changes to HydraBBS between V1.10 and V1.11"

  Changes to HydraBBS between V1.10 and V1.11
  ===========================================

  Please read *ALL* of this file, or you won't know about some of the great
  new features of this release.

  Go on, it'll only take you a couple of minutes.

  This document is stored as HBBS:Docs/Misc/Upgrades/Changes_To_V1.11.Guide

  Details
  =======

  Sysop Information     - @{"More..." link SysopInformation}

  Developer Information - @{"More..." link HBBS:Developer/Docs/Upgrades/Dev_Changes_V1.11.guide/MAIN}

  Files Changed         - @{"More..." link FilesChanged}

@EndNode

@Node SysopInformation "Sysop Information"

  Sysop Information
  =================

  I'd just like to point out that my coding skills kick ass....

  * HBBSMultiTop

    You'll love me...  I know it...

    HBBSMULTITOP NOW CREATES CONFTOP SCREENS!

    Told ya. :^)

    And god damn, the things I had to do to code it..

    check this out:

    /* overview of how to access data for conf weektop.

    TopBWeekConfUploaders list               (struct List)
      conf 1 week uploaders list             (struct ConfListNode)  (first node in List)
        userlist                             (struct List)
          usernode                           (struct UserNode) (first node in userlist)
            UserInfo                         (struct UserInfo)
              confstats list                 (struct List)
                conf info <-- use this one   (struct ConfInfo) (first node in confstats list)
                conf info
                conf info
          usernode
            ...

      conf 2 week uploaders list
        userlist
          usernode
            UserInfo
              confstats list
                conf info
                conf info <-- use this one
                conf info
            usernode
              ...

    */

    Talk about nodes in lists in a structure in a nodes in lists in nodes in lists,
    but this is getting silly..

    And if you can understand that, then you'll know what I mean and just how
    good I am..  And if you don't understand, they it doesn't matter, just use
    the damn software... :-)

    Added a FROM option so you can create a file with a list of files to
    process rather than specifiying them all on a *very* long command line.

    Added loads of error messages

    Added a load of new @^@ codes

    Checked and debugged with Enforcer and CodeWatcher, there are no memory
    leaks any more.

    Speeded up creation of the user lists in memory by locking the user data
    file and reading all the data from it in one go, rather than by using
    HBBS_LoadUser() which keeps locking, opening, seeking, reading and closing
    the data file.  So now it's loads quicker if you've got lots of users!

    Fixed some @^@ codes that weren't working prior to V1.11.

    Created some (very nice) example conftop screens for conferences 2 and 3
    for the example configs, see HBBS:Storage/Example_Configs/

    Read the docs for more info and installation of the stats generator counterpart

  * FrontEnd

    Uh

    Uh

    Uh

    Uhhhh...  I just spunked over it..

    Erm, sorry 'bout that. (Hydra removes white sticky stuff from keyboard
    and screen)..

    Right...

    Because I'm so fantastically GREAT, I've updated this door.  So now you
    can create a screen and get the door to ask for a username and password
    wthout distrubing on-screen ansi.  So you can create screens like:

    -- cut here --

          @^16.16^BBSNAME@ @^TIME@ @^DATE@

      Username : [ ------------------------- ]
      Password : [ ------------------------- ]

    -- cut here --

    And put the prompt for the username and password where the '-'s begin
    using ansi cursor position (ESC[r;cH) (row,column e.g. y,x not x,y)

    Now is that something to spank the money over or what ?


    Check out the example BBSTitle.TXT and Frontend.CFG files in:
    HBBS:Storage/Example_Screens/Utopia

    See the docs for more info: HBBS:Docs/Doors/FrontEng.Guide/MAIN

  * Node

    Implemented File,Path and CallsThisWeek @^@ screen codes and documented
    Time/Date/File/Path in the list of supported @^@ codes
    (see HBBS:Docs/Reference/Screens.Guide/SupportedItems)

    Tweaked the operation of the GL_NODISTURB GetLine() tag so that the
    background colour of the text is preserved.

    Fixed the combination of the passwordchar GetLine() parameter and
    the GL_EDIT flag.  Previously, you could enter a password
    then use the left and right cursor keys to insert letters, but
    instead of the password character being displayed (e.g. '*') the
    actual key would be displayed (oops!)  so you might see "***b***"
    instead of "*******".  Probably not something you'd ever notice
    anyway..

    If GL_NODISTURB was used and you pressed Ctrl-X to erase the line
    the entire line would be erased, now when you press ctrl-x only
    the text you've typed in will be erased.

    DOOR_GetLine() and the GL_NODISTURB flag now works great with the
    improved frontend door after of these changes!

  * Node/Control/HBBSCommon.library/HBBSNode.library

    Fixed interprocess communication, free'd memory was being referenced
    after messages were sent, sometimes causing the node to hang or
    other un-predicdable results.

    So I guess HydraBBS just got even more stable.

    I spent a good few hours going over all the messaging routines with
    a fine toothcombe so there shouldn't be any more problems relating
    to messaging now.  Hopefully.

    No-one else seems to have noticed this mind you..

  * CheckFiles

    Fixed bug where it would pass the control program a null pointer
    for a filename if you deleted a file from the playpen while it was
    checking other files.  This caused the Node program to cause
    enforcer hits.

  * HBBSCommon.library

    Changed the HBBS_GetAmigaTime() so it doesn't require a battery
    backed up clock.  (might speed things up a bit too...)

    HBBS_GetTime, HBBS_GetDate and HBBS_GetDateString now return
    a pointer to the string they produce (which is the same as
    the paramater they're passed) so you can do stuff like:

    char MyDate[LEN_DATESTR+1];

    puts( HBBS_GetDate(MyDate) );

    HBBS_LogError() now uses a different time/date format:
    "DD-MMM-YYYY HH:MM:SS" instead of "DAY MMM DD HH:MM:SS YYYY"

    This is so that it's easier to scan the log files that use
    this function.

    Changed remaining routines that used ReadBattClock() to use
    HBBS_GetAmigaTime().

  * StatsGenerator

    Created this door, which is currently only called by AddCreds
    to add credits to a per-user stats file, for use with HBBSMultiTop
    (or any other program that wants the stats...)

  * AddCreds

    Changed the format of the log file that it produces.

    Now it's even easier to create weektops/conftops etc from it's
    log files.

    Now logs data for uploaded files into HBBS:Logs/Upload.LOG and
    HBBS:system/Data/Users/<UserID>/Upload.LOG.

    (for easy retrival by stats gathering programs/doors)

  * Docs

    Documented BBSColours.CFG.

  * HBBSNode.library

    Adjusted the HBBS_SetCols() routine to translate {E}'s into an escape
    character for the BBSColours.CFG file

  * MailScan and MailRead

    Oops, I fudged it so that a user couldn't quit if they didn't have
    any messages witht the MustRead flag set.  Fixed!

@EndNode

